HEADWORD: Subumbrella
<hw>Sub`um*brel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The integument of the under surface of the bell, or disk-shaped
body, of a jellyfish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subundation</ent>⟦br⟧
